Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Place sealed bag of @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} in microwave and microwave
until mostly cooked through and easily pierced with a knife, ~{5-7%minutes}.

While potatoes cook, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Pick and roughly chop fronds from
@dill{1/4%ounce}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; chop leaves
into bite-size pieces. Halve @tomato{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-
thick half-moons.

Open bag of potatoes (careful—steam will be released!), add a drizzle of
@cooking oil{}, and toss to coat. Transfer potatoes to an oiled #baking sheet{}
and spread out in an even layer. Using the bottom of a #glass{} or a
#potato masher{}, smash each potato until 1⁄2 inch thick. Drizzle with oil and
season generously with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and as much lemon zest as you like.

Roast potatoes on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Flip potatoes during the last 5 minutes of roasting so they get crispy on
> both sides.

While potatoes roast, heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too
quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to
handle, roughly chop.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @smoky garlic herb sauce{1%ounce},
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, juice from half the
lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), and as much dill as you like.

Once potatoes are done, let cool slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss lettuce, tomato, and potatoes with as much dressing
as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide salad between bowls and top with bacon. Serve with any remaining lemon
wedges on the side.